cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper discusses recent work on neural-based models in automatic text summarization, which falls under the category of natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the use of neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses related techniques such as information retrieval, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and the use of deep learning, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
